arly quasi-2D metallic conductivity is dominated by nonmagnetic Co(1) and\nCo(2) sites. Consequently, unique magneto-transport phenomena observed in\nSrCo6O11 are demonstrated owing to the interaction between the conduction\nelectrons at the Co(1) and Co(2) sites and the local moments at Co(3) sites.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 26 Jul 2006 10:51:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2012-03-22"}
